### Medical Test
$P(D) = {{prev}}$
$P(+ \mid D) = {{sens}}$
$P(+ \mid \overline{D}) = {{fpr}}$
---
**Per 100,000 people:**
With disease: {{toFixed(prev*100000,0)}}
True positives: {{toFixed(prev*sens*100000,1)}}
False positives: {{toFixed((1-prev)*fpr*100000,1)}}
Total positives: {{toFixed((prev*sens+(1-prev)*fpr)*100000,1)}}
---
$P(D \mid +) = {{toFixed(prev*sens/(prev*sens+(1-prev)*fpr)*100,1)}}\%$
---
{{prev*sens/(prev*sens+(1-prev)*fpr) < 0.1 ? 'Surprise: most positives are FALSE alarms!' : prev*sens/(prev*sens+(1-prev)*fpr) < 0.5 ? 'Still mostly false positives' : 'Majority are true positives'}}

### Tornado Warning
$P(T) = {{pTorn}}$
$P(\text{radar} \mid T) = {{pDet}}$
$P(\text{radar} \mid \overline{T}) = {{pFal}}$
---
**Per 5,000 storm alerts:**
Real tornadoes: {{toFixed(pTorn*5000,1)}}
True alarms: {{toFixed(pTorn*pDet*5000,1)}}
False alarms: {{toFixed((1-pTorn)*pFal*5000,1)}}
Total radar signals: {{toFixed((pTorn*pDet+(1-pTorn)*pFal)*5000,1)}}
---
$P(T \mid \text{radar}) = {{toFixed(pTorn*pDet/(pTorn*pDet+(1-pTorn)*pFal)*100,1)}}\%$
---
{{pTorn*pDet/(pTorn*pDet+(1-pTorn)*pFal) > 0.5 ? 'Issue warning (>50%)' : 'Mostly false alarms (<50%)'}}
